Adult/immature.description: Black Swifts are much larger than Vaux's Swifts with darker underparts and a slower flight style.
Chimney Swifts look very similar but their ranges do not overlap; Chimney in the East and Vaux's in the West.

Adult.description: Swallows have shorter, less curved and more triangular-shaped wings than swifts. They also have deeper wingbeats that the fluttery flight style of swifts. Northern Rough-winged Swallows, in particular have paler underparts than Chimney Swifts.
